libbc-runtime (1.2.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * refactor(log): migrer bc_runtime_log + log_drain sur bc_core_writer
    (Phase 2.5 audit 2026-04-23). Factoriser format_record_into_buffer.
    write(2) atomique per-record, <= PIPE_BUF. API inchangee.
  * refactor(error_collector): migrer flush_to_stderr sur bc_core_writer.
    Elimine fprintf/stdio du hot path.
  * test(error_collector): suite unitaire cmocka complete.
  * fix(log): checker le retour de format_timestamp dans log_drain (P1).
  * ci: ajouter release+test et valgrind memcheck (P1).
  * test(memcheck): bumper simple_tests timeout 30->60s pour accomoder
    competition parallele valgrind.
  * docs: clarifier l'invariant log sink.
  * Requires libbc-core-dev >= 1.4.0 (module I/O writer/reader/fmt).

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Fri, 24 Apr 2026 09:30:00 +0100

libbc-runtime (1.1.2-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * chore(cppcheck): mirror src/<dir>/*.c suppressions without the `*/`
    prefix so cppcheck 2.13 (Ubuntu 24.04 runner) matches the same
    paths as 2.17+ (local). 2.13 did not expand `*` across an empty
    leading segment, so `src/config/foo.c` escaped `*/src/config/*.c`
    and tripped the unusedFunction check on get_integer/get_boolean.

 -- Younes Benmoussa <younes.benmoussa@pm.me>  Thu, 23 Apr 2026 10:50:00 +0100

